BOUT++ python visualisation routines

Dependencies
======================

o Scipy/Numpy			For loading NetCDF files, arrays
o Mayavi2		    	For creating the visualisations
o BOUT collection routines  	Loading in the data

Recommended
======================

o IPython			Mayavi2 scripts run better within IPython over the default interpreter

Scripts available
======================

o mlab.py

Plots up to 2 scalar fields against each other, one in a volume and
the other as slices evenly distributed.

o vis/vis2.py

Generates an interactive plot that can contain many different time
slices.  Has ability to select fewer data points to increase speed of
plotting

o fmlab.py

A callable function that generates a plot similar to that by mlab.py